episodes.overview: After the queens perform one-woman shows, Jackie Cox calls out Jaida Essence Hall for not being honest on the runway, and Whoopi Goldberg shares her words of wisdom.

episodes.name: Viva Drag Vegas
episodes.overview: After performing a Las Vegas-style musical medley in the season's last challenge, the queens reflect on their Top Five status and relive their favorite Untucked moments.

11.name: Season 11

episodes.overview: After a challenging group performance, the queens size up the competition. While a queen gets called out for being safe, the bottom queens face the fact that one of them might be going home tonight.

episodes.name: The Bag Ball
episodes.overview: After the Bag Ball, some of the safe queens question the tops, Kandy Muse offers up (more) unsolicited advice to Elliott with 2 Ts, and Tamisha Iman gets blunt about her competition.

episodes.overview: After the queens star in a social media-themed musical, Olivia Lux does a backstage ruveal, Rose and Denali clear the air after fighting over a role, and the bottoms prepare for battle.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: The queens weigh in on each other's Snatch Game performances, Olivia Lux and Rose question Utica's unflattering off-camera behavior, and Ts Madison drops by for a pep talk.

episodes.name: Freaky Friday Queens
episodes.overview: After the makeover challenge, the queens vent over having to call out one of their sisters, Denali and Olivia Lux get emotional at the idea of leaving, and Kandy Muse gets a moving message.

episodes.name: Pop! Goes the Queens
episodes.overview: After a soda branding challenge, Olivia Lux admits she feels overlooked, the queens reveal their top competition, and Tina Burner gets a message from her mom.

episodes.overview: After the roast challenge, Gottmik reflects on her growth in the competition, and former Miss Congeniality winners Nina West, Valentina and Heidi N Closet drop in to chat with the queens.

episodes.name: Henny, I Shrunk the Drag Queens!
episodes.overview: After their star turns in a sci-fi spoof, Olivia Lux feels the sting of the other queens' critiques, Kandy Muse needs medical attention, and Cynthia Erivo pops in to chat with the girls.

episodes.name: Gettin' Lucky
episodes.overview: After performing in the season's last challenge, the queens react to seeing their baby photos and addressing their younger selves, and Rose and Symone receive messages of support from home.

12.name: Season 12

episodes.overview: Seven new queens untuck and hash out the struggles of their first week in the competition. After hearing the others' stories, one queen shares how her drag journey is different from theirs.

episodes.overview: With all the Season 14 queens together for the first time, the kiki heats up and cracks in the sisterhood begin to show.

episodes.overview: The Maxi Challenge has the queens in their feelings as they discuss the week's placements. Emotions run raw, putting their sisterly bonds to the test.

episodes.name: Catwalk
episodes.overview: After performing in their final challenge, the queens discuss addressing their younger selves, rate their chances of making the finale, and recall their favorite moments of the competition.

13.name: Season 13
13.overview: An access-all-areas pass to the drama that you didn't see on the runway of the fourteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race.

episodes.name: One Night Only (1)
episodes.overview: The cameras go backstage to meet the 16 new queens as they prepare to introduce themselves to the world in their werk room entrances and begin their first challenge.

episodes.name: One Night Only (2)
episodes.overview: The queens take time to get to know each other after a talent show challenge, Ariana Grande visits backstage, and the first to depart lets her voice be heard before her sashay.

episodes.name: All Queens Go to Heaven
episodes.overview: After the queens film ads for Heaven, Mistress Isabelle Brooks gives makeup advice, Princess Poppy explains her approach to the competition, and Maren Morris doles out words of wisdom.

episodes.name: Supersized Snatch Game

episodes.name: House of Fashion
episodes.overview: The queens are stitched, glued and gooped after turning home dÃ©cor into haute couture. A kiki with Janelle MonÃ¡e reminds them how inspiring they are to others.

episodes.name: Old Friends Gold
episodes.overview: The temperature rises backstage following a heated Girl Group challenge that leaves the queens shaken, rattled and rolled. Sage advice from some old friends remind our queens of the importance of friends and chosen family.

episodes.name: The Daytona Wind 2
episodes.overview: After the winds settle the queens untuck and discuss the art of comedic timing. Harvey Guillen drops in and gives the queens some valuable advice.

episodes.overview: The queens yuck it up backstage following the comedy challenge, but the laughter soon gives way to tears. Comedian Ali Wong stops by for a kiki with the queens.

episodes.name: Wigloose: The Rusical!

episodes.name: Blame It on the Edit

14.name: Season 14
14.overview: An access-all-areas pass to the drama that you didn't see on the runway of the fifteenth season of RuPaul's Drag Race.

episodes.name: Rate-A-Queen
episodes.overview: The queens toast to a new season and discuss Xunami Muse's catchy song, Mirage's fabulous dance moves and O's stunning costume, and guest judge Charlize Theron joins for a heart-to-heart.

episodes.name: Queen Choice Awards
episodes.overview: The queens unwind and discuss Mhi'ya Iman LePaige's showstopping flips, Nymphia Wind's gag-worthy ruveal, and Megami's solemn performance, and Becky G drops in with encouraging words.

episodes.name: The Mother of All Balls
episodes.overview: The lounge gets tense as the queens offer each other brutally honest and unsolicited critiques, and the first to be eliminated proudly stands by her runway looks.

episodes.name: RDR Live!
episodes.overview: RDR Live! served up plenty of jokes, but it's no laughing matter when an ongoing conflict resurfaces, and Sarah Michelle Gellar crashes the party and slays the queens.

episodes.name: Girl Groups
episodes.overview: After a gag-worthy performance, the winning girl group revels in their victory, Q hits a nerve when she critiques Xunami Muse, and Icona Pop drops in for a visit.

episodes.name: Welcome to the DollHouse
episodes.overview: The queens discover that some amongst them are shadier than others following the week's design challenge, and fashion icon Law Roach drops in with some critiques.

episodes.name: The Sound of Rusic
episodes.overview: After performing in a rusical, tensions are high as the queens compare choreography and debate who had the most steps in the Swish Alps, and Adam Shankman drops in for a kiki.

episodes.name: Snatch Game
episodes.overview: Fallout from Snatch Game is anything but a laughing matter as the queens discuss who scored and who flopped, and Kyra Sedgwick stops by to remind everyone that attitude is everything.

episodes.name: See You Next Wednesday
episodes.overview: After the spooky design challenge, the queens are coming apart at the seams, and runway model Kaia Gerber sashays in for a fashionable kiki.

episodes.name: Werk the World
episodes.overview: Things get funky in the Untucked Lounge when the queens ponder the power of their Werq the World performances, and Jamal Sims struts in to break it down for them.

episodes.name: Corporate Queens
episodes.overview: After their critiques, the queens settle in and have a kiki with Joel Kim Booster about the magic of drag, and a video from home has everyone feeling their emotions.

episodes.name: Bathroom Hunties
episodes.overview: After the queens design and showcase bathrooms, Plane Jane gets vulnerable, the girls talk teamwork, and Mayan Lopez pops by with some much needed relief.

episodes.name: Drag Race Vegas LIVE! Makeovers
episodes.overview: After their critiques on the makeovers of dancers from RuPaul's Drag Race LIVE! in Las Vegas, the queens praise Kelsea Ballerini for being a strong ally.

episodes.name: Booked & Blessed
episodes.overview: After their critiques, the queens reflect on the last challenge ahead of the finals, and Ts Madison stops by to offer words of encouragement.
